{
  "texts": [
    "(12)This category hasObjects = [ω g] -twisted (d -1)-representations of the centralizer H g ⊆ G (0) of g,(13) where[ω g] ∈ H d (H g, ×),(14)is obtained from the information of the 't Hooft anomaly [ω] ∈ H d+1 (G (0), ×) for the G (0) 0-form symmetry and the symmetry element g ∈ G (0) by performing what is known as a slant product.",
    "See section 5.2 for more details.Expanding out this statement in more detail, we have 1.",
    "(d -2)-charges of operators lying at the boundary ofD (g) d-1 are [ω g]-twisted (d -1)- representations of H g, or in other words 0-morphisms in (d -1)-Rep [ω g] (H g). 2.",
    "For 1 ≤ r ≤ d -2, we have that the (d -r -2)-charges going from a (d -r -1)-charge described by an (r -1)-morphism M r-1 ∈ (d -1)-Rep [ω g] (H g) to a (d -r -1)-charge described by an (r -1)-morphism M ′ r-1 ∈ (d -1)-Rep [ω g] (H g), are described by the r-morphisms from M r-1 to M ′ r-1 in (d -1)-Rep [ω g] (H g).The above statement only incorporates the action of the centralizerH g. Consider a (d -r -2)- dimensional g-twisted sector operator O d-r-2 carrying a (d -r -2)-charge described by an r-morphism M r ∈ (d -1)-Rep [ω g] (H g).",
    "Acting on O d-r-2 by an element h ̸ ∈ H g, we obtain a (d -r -2)-dimensional operator O ′ d-r-2 in hgh -1 -twisted sector carrying an isomorphic (d -r -2)-charge described by an r-morphism M ′ r ∈ (d -1)-Rep [ω hgh -1] (H hgh -1)."
  ]
